  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Through FY2026 to date the federal government has obligated $5.3B for NAICS 541611 Administrative Management and General Management Consulting Services. That total comes from 9,051 awards with an average award size of $582K and is down 53.4% year over year. Obligations have varied over recent fiscal years: FY21 totaled $13.3B, FY22 totaled $12.9B, FY23 totaled $14.2B, FY24 totaled $15B, and FY25 totaled $11.3B. In the current fiscal year to date the largest buying agencies are the Department of Defense ($1.3B) and the Department of Health and Human Services ($1.1B), while the largest single vendors are led by DELOITTE CONSULTING LLP ($380M) and BOOZ ALLEN HAMILTON INC ($210M). The current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date) and reflect contract obligations recorded so far in FY2026.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How has federal spending on NAICS 541611 changed recently?",
        "body": "Obligations fell 53.4% year over year to $5.3B in FY2026 to date. Annual obligations ranged from $12.9B to $15B between FY22 and FY24, with prior totals of $13.3B in FY21 and $11.3B in FY25, showing higher full-year activity before the current partial-year total."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors account for the largest FY2026 to date obligations?",
        "body": "The largest buying agencies in FY2026 to date are the Department of Defense ($1.3B) and the Department of Health and Human Services ($1.1B), followed by the Department of Homeland Security ($496M) and the Department of State ($365M). The largest vendors in FY2026 to date are DELOITTE CONSULTING LLP ($380M), BOOZ ALLEN HAMILTON INC ($210M), and LMI CONSULTING, LLC ($209M)."
      }
    ]
  },
